{"type":"user","uuid":"d88c048c-88ff-467d-aa50-9ddf4417806a","session_id":"9310a036-0fcf-4395-9365-74ce968ab0f4","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cdeb407ff468dd4921b8d49e24952","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks for F-007 (Test and Validation Suite) have been completed. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Setup Phase (T-001 ~ T-009) ✅\n- Created `tests/fixtures/` directory structure with plan and state fixtures\n- Created valid plan fixtures (feature-list, bug-fix-list)\n- Created invalid plan fixtures (missing schema, bad JSON, missing fields, type errors)\n- Created pipeline state fixtures (idle, running, completed, failed)\n- Created test helper modules:\n  - `fixture-loader.js` - Lazy loading utilities for test fixtures\n  - `mock-runner.js` - Mock script runner with state tracking\n  - `mock-telegram.js` - Mock Telegraf context for command handler tests\n  - `test-state.js` - Temporary state management for integration tests\n- Updated `package.json` with layered test scripts (`test:unit`, `test:integration`, `test:coverage`)\n\n### Foundational Phase (T-010 ~ T-011) ✅\n- Mock runner supports response sequencing\n- Mock Telegram supports document upload\n\n### US-1: Command Parsing & Routing Tests (T-101 ~ T-104) ✅\n- Enhanced parser tests with edge cases, unicode, long input handling\n- Enhanced registry tests with lookup error paths and complex metadata\n- Enhanced validator tests with boundary conditions\n- Enhanced formatter tests with output scenarios\n\n### US-2: Control Layer Return Tests (T-111 ~ T-114) ✅\n- Enhanced pipeline-control-service tests\n- Enhanced pipeline-controller tests\n- Enhanced plan-ingestion-service tests\n- Created `tests/services/error-paths.test.js` for error handling\n\n### US-3: E2E Integration Tests (T-121 ~ T-124) ✅\n- Created `tests/integration/e2e-main-chain.test.js` with start→status→stop chain tests\n- Added duplicate start prevention tests\n- Added stop when not running tests\n- Added state transition verification\n\n### US-4: Plan File Validation Tests (T-131 ~ T-137) ✅\n- Created `tests/services/plan-version.test.js` for version management\n- Created `tests/integration/plan-version-flow.test.js` for integration tests\n\n### US-5: Permission & Security Tests (T-141 ~ T-149) ✅\n- Existing tests already cover admin/operator/viewer boundaries\n- Existing tests cover high-risk commands (stop, reset, force-unlock)\n- Existing tests cover param sanitization\n- Existing tests cover confirmation manager\n- Existing `tests/integration/security-flow.test.js` covers security flow\n\n### Polish Phase (T-901 ~ T-903) ✅\n- Created `tests/README.md` documenting test coverage\n- Verified all tests pass (exit code 0)\n- Updated `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` with F-007 decision\n\nAll tests pass successfully using `npm test`.\n\n[Agent ID: agent-ec7fda9f]"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb407ff468dd4921b8d49e24952","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:12:44.999Z","_requestId":"f8b0d56a051a42089a34cee3b1b65359"}
