{"type":"assistant","uuid":"2026031205125253f28d0e0eea46e3","session_id":"9310a036-0fcf-4395-9365-74ce968ab0f4","message":{"id":"2026031205125253f28d0e0eea46e3","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019cdebee0a7a48270ad971678c4a199","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/007-test-and-validation-suite/tasks.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":10958,"output_tokens":314,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdebebf5d85e280e638ca4e1c1068","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:12:57.772Z","_requestId":"f8b0d56a051a42089a34cee3b1b65359"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"ea1f19fa-ea66-4c2b-b950-f4b5037acc56","session_id":"9310a036-0fcf-4395-9365-74ce968ab0f4","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cdebed9c7b9712e7f38adbeb67376","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-reviewer\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated quality reviewer. Uses prizmkit.analyze for cross-document consistency, prizmkit.code-review for spec compliance and code quality, and writes integration tests. Use when performing analysis, testing, or code review.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-code-review, prizmkit-analyze, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Reviewer Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的质量审查员。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"质检员 + 校对员\"——不生产产品但确保质量，负责两个阶段的工作：\n  14→1. **交叉校验（Phase 4）**: 在实现前用 `prizmkit.analyze` 检查 spec/plan/tasks 的一致性\n  15→2. **评审（Phase 6）**: 在实现后用 `prizmkit.code-review` 检查代码质量，编写和执行集成测试\n  16→\n  17→### 项目上下文\n  18→\n  19→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。审查前先读 `root.prizm` 了解项目规则（RULES）、模式（PATTERNS）和已知陷阱（TRAPS），需要时读取模块级文档。\n  20→\n  21→### 制品路径\n  22→\n  23→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  24→|------|------|\n  25→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  26→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md |\n  27→\n  28→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  29→\n  30→1. Phase 4 时运行 `prizmkit.analyze` 做交叉一致性校验\n  31→2. Phase 6 时运行 `prizmkit.code-review` 做规格合规和代码质量审查\n  32→3. Phase 6 时编写和执行集成测试，验证模块间交互\n  33→4. 验证实际实现是否符合 plan.md 中的接口设计\n  34→5. 验证跨模块数据流的完整性和正确性\n  35→6. 测试边界条件和异常路径\n  36→7. 检查代码是否符合 `.prizm-docs/` RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  37→8. 审查是**只读操作**（Phase 4 和 Phase 6 的审查部分不修改代码文件）\n  38→9. 集成测试用例必须覆盖 spec.md 定义的所有用户故事\n  39→\n  40→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  41→\n  42→- 不编写实现代码（Dev 的职责）\n  43→- 不分解任务（PM 的职责）\n  44→- 不进行任务调度（Coordinator 的职责）\n  45→\n  46→### 行为规则\n  47→\n  48→```\n  49→REV-01: Phase 4 使用 prizmkit.analyze 做交叉校验\n  50→REV-02: Phase 6 使用 prizmkit.code-review 做代码审查\n  51→REV-03: 每个发现必须引用具体的文件路径和行号\n  52→REV-04: CRITICAL 级别发现必须包含具体的修复建议\n  53→REV-05: 最多 30 个发现（保持可操作性）\n  54→REV-06: Spec compliance 失败始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  55→REV-07: 安全发现始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  56→REV-08: 集成测试必须覆盖 spec.md 所有用户故事\n  57→REV-09: 审查代码是否符合 .prizm-docs/ PATTERNS 和 RULES\n  58→```\n  59→\n  60→### Phase 4 工作流程：交叉校验\n  61→\n  62→**前置条件**: PM 已完成 spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md\n  63→\n  64→1. 运行 `prizmkit.analyze`（只读）\n  65→   - 输入: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n  66→   - 6 个检测通道: 重复检测、歧义检测、不完整检测、Prizm 规则对齐、覆盖缺口、不一致性\n  67→   - 输出: 一致性分析报告（仅对话输出）\n  68→2. 如发现 CRITICAL 问题，报告给 Coordinator 退回 PM 修复\n  69→3. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含分析结果）\n  70→\n  71→### Phase 6 工作流程：评审\n  72→\n  73→**前置条件**: Dev 已完成实现，所有任务标记 `[x]`\n  74→\n  75→1. 读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm`，重点关注 RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  76→2. 运行 `prizmkit.code-review`（只读）\n  77→   - 6 个审查维度: 规格符合度、计划遵循度、代码质量、安全性、一致性、测试覆盖\n  78→   - 判定: PASS | PASS WITH WARNINGS | NEEDS FIXES\n  79→3. 编写和执行集成测试:\n  80→   - 接口合规性（请求格式、响应格式）\n  81→   - 跨模块数据流完整性\n  82→   - 用户故事验收标准（来自 spec.md）\n  83→   - 边界条件和异常路径\n  84→4. 生成统一评审报告\n  85→5. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）\n  86→\n  87→### 判定标准\n  88→\n  89→| 判定 | 条件 | 后续动作 |\n  90→|------|------|---------|\n  91→| **PASS** | 无 CRITICAL 或 HIGH 发现 | 进入下一阶段 |\n  92→| **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS** | 无 CRITICAL，有 HIGH 发现 | 记录待改进项，可进入下一阶段 |\n  93→| **NEEDS_FIXES** | 存在 CRITICAL 发现 | 退回 Dev 修复后重新评审 |\n  94→\n  95→### 严重级别\n  96→\n  97→| 级别 | 定义 | 示例 |\n  98→|------|------|------|\n  99→| CRITICAL | 安全风险或严重架构问题 | SQL 注入、硬编码密钥 |\n 100→| HIGH | 影响可维护性的显著问题 | 规格不符、大量重复代码 |\n 101→| MEDIUM | 代码质量改进点 | 命名不统一、缺少注释 |\n 102→| LOW | 风格建议 | 格式微调、可选优化 |\n 103→\n 104→### 异常处理\n 105→\n 106→| 场景 | 策略 |\n 107→|------|------|\n 108→| analyze 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 PM 修复 |\n 109→| code-review 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 Dev 修复 |\n 110→| 集成测试失败 | 分类严重级别 → ISSUE_REPORT → Coordinator 派发给 Dev |\n 111→| 审查发现超过 30 个 | 只保留最严重的 30 个 |\n 112→| Prizm RULES 违规 | 自动标记为 CRITICAL |\n 113→\n 114→### 通信规则\n 115→\n 116→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Coordinator。\n 117→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）标志完成\n 118→- 发送 ISSUE_REPORT 报告 CRITICAL 发现\n 119→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 120→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdebebf5d85e280e638ca4e1c1068","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:12:57.773Z","_requestId":"f8b0d56a051a42089a34cee3b1b65359"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"7dc1c7f1-092d-43e3-8507-5a61c01843ee","session_id":"9310a036-0fcf-4395-9365-74ce968ab0f4","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cdebedb7fbc5097ac2fc2b8a20c41","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n   2→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n   3→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n   4→ADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\n   5→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n   6→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n   7→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n   8→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n   9→DOC_STATUS: initialized\n  10→ASSESSMENT: ASSESSMENT.md\n  11→MIGRATION_CANDIDATE: docs/AI_CONTEXT -> not_found\n  12→\n  13→MODULE_INDEX:\n  14→- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n  15→- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n  16→- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n  17→- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n  18→- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n  19→\n  20→LOAD_RULES:\n  21→- ON_SESSION_START: read .prizm-docs/root.prizm\n  22→- ON_TASK: load related L1 via MODULE_INDEX\n  23→- ON_EDIT: load/create related L2 lazily\n  24→\n  25→DEPENDENCY_HEALTH:\n  26→- outdated_major: dotenv,express,zod\n  27→- npm_audit_prod: 0 vulnerabilities\n  28→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdebebf5d85e280e638ca4e1c1068","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:12:57.774Z","_requestId":"f8b0d56a051a42089a34cee3b1b65359"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"5cc0d815-06e0-4934-a50e-26d2f6d26965","session_id":"9310a036-0fcf-4395-9365-74ce968ab0f4","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cdebedcfe87a5d899ed2d843aefac","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-007: Test and Validation Suite\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→建立 Telegram 管道能力的测试体系，覆盖命令路由、计划文件接入、进程控制、状态聚合与权限校验。使用 Node.js 内置 test runner，补充单元与集成测试，确保核心流程在改动后可回归验证。\n   6→\n   7→**Dependencies**: F-003 (Plan Ingestion), F-004 (Pipeline Controller), F-005 (Status & Logs), F-006 (Safety Guard) — all completed\n   8→\n   9→---\n  10→\n  11→## User Stories\n  12→\n  13→### US-1: Command Parsing & Routing Tests\n  14→\n  15→**As a** 开发者 **I want** 命令解析与路由层有完整单元测试 **So that** 命令格式变化时可快速验证正确性\n  16→\n  17→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  18→- AC-1.1: 覆盖命令解析器 (parser) 所有分支：正常命令、空参数、非法格式\n  19→- AC-1.2: 覆盖命令注册表 (registry) 查找与错误路径\n  20→- AC-1.3: 覆盖参数校验器 (validator) 边界条件\n  21→- AC-1.4: 覆盖响应格式化器 (formatter) 各种输出场景\n  22→\n  23→---\n  24→\n  25→### US-2: Control Layer Return Tests\n  26→\n  27→**As a** 开发者 **I want** 控制层 API 有完整测试覆盖 **So that** 返回结构与错误码变更时可防止回归\n  28→\n  29→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  30→- AC-2.1: 覆盖 pipeline-control-service 所有方法返回结构\n  31→- AC-2.2: 覆盖 pipeline-controller (F-004) 并发锁与状态管理\n  32→- AC-2.3: 覆盖 plan-ingestion-service 校验与版本管理逻辑\n  33→- AC-2.4: 所有错误路径有对应测试用例\n  34→\n  35→---\n  36→\n  37→### US-3: E2E Integration Test\n  38→\n  39→**As a** 运维人员 **I want** 有一条端到端集成测试验证主链路 **So that** 我可以确信核心流程在部署后可用\n  40→\n  41→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  42→- AC-3.1: 测试 start → status → stop 主链路（mock 外部依赖）\n  43→- AC-3.2: 验证状态流转正确：idle → running → stopped\n  44→- AC-3.3: 验证错误处理：重复启动、空停止等边界场景\n  45→- AC-3.4: 测试运行时间 < 30s，可加入 pre-commit hook\n  46→\n  47→---\n  48→\n  49→### US-4: Plan File Validation Tests\n  50→\n  51→**As a** 开发者 **I want** 计划文件校验与版本切换有自动化测试 **So that** 上传流程变更时可防止回归\n  52→\n  53→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  54→- AC-4.1: 覆盖 JSON schema 校验：合法文件、缺失字段、类型错误\n  55→- AC-4.2: 覆盖版本管理：上传、列表、切换、回滚\n  56→- AC-4.3: 覆盖版本切换边界：不存在的版本、损坏的版本文件\n  57→- AC-4.4: 测试与 pipeline 集成点：动态切换计划文件路径\n  58→\n  59→---\n  60→\n  61→### US-5: Permission & Security Negative Tests\n  62→\n  63→**As a** 安全审计员 **I want** 权限与安全策略有负向测试 **So that** 未授权操作被阻断验证\n  64→\n  65→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  66→- AC-5.1: 覆盖权限分级检查：admin/operator/viewer 各级别边界\n  67→- AC-5.2: 覆盖高风险命令拦截：stop/reset/retry/exec 权限不足场景\n  68→- AC-5.3: 覆盖参数净化：路径穿越、shell 注入、危险字符\n  69→- AC-5.4: 覆盖确认机制：超时取消、强制跳过 (--force)\n  70→\n  71→---\n  72→\n  73→## Non-Functional Requirements\n  74→\n  75→### NFR-1: Performance\n  76→- 单元测试套件运行 < 10s\n  77→- 集成测试套件运行 < 60s\n  78→- 测试可并行执行\n  79→\n  80→### NFR-2: Coverage\n  81→- 核心模块行覆盖率 > 80%\n  82→- 关键路径 (happy path) 100% 覆盖\n  83→- 错误路径 > 70% 覆盖\n  84→\n  85→### NFR-3: Maintainability\n  86→- 测试文件与源文件结构对应\n  87→- 使用统一的 mock/stub 策略\n  88→- 测试数据集中管理\n  89→\n  90→---\n  91→\n  92→## Scope Boundaries\n  93→\n  94→### In Scope\n  95→- 补充缺失的单元测试\n  96→- 新增集成测试覆盖主链路\n  97→- 负向测试覆盖安全策略\n  98→- 测试工具函数与 fixtures\n  99→- CI 集成（package.json scripts）\n 100→\n 101→### Out of Scope\n 102→- 性能/压力测试\n 103→- 端到端 UI 测试\n 104→- 外部服务 mock（Telegram API）改为单元测试\n 105→- 代码覆盖率报告服务集成\n 106→\n 107→---\n 108→\n 109→## Test Matrix\n 110→\n 111→| Area | Test Type | Priority | Target File |\n 112→|------|-----------|----------|-------------|\n 113→| Command Parser | Unit | High | tests/bot/commands/parser.test.js |\n 114→| Command Registry | Unit | High | tests/bot/commands/registry.test.js |\n 115→| Param Validator | Unit | High | tests/bot/commands/validator.test.js |\n 116→| Response Formatter | Unit | Medium | tests/bot/commands/formatter.test.js |\n 117→| Pipeline Controller | Unit | High | tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js |\n 118→| Plan Ingestion | Unit | High | tests/services/plan-ingestion-service.test.js |\n 119→| Status Aggregator | Unit | High | tests/services/status-aggregator.test.js |\n 120→| Permission Guard | Unit | High | tests/security/permission-guard.test.js |\n 121→| Param Sanitizer | Unit | High | tests/security/param-sanitizer.test.js |\n 122→| Confirmation Manager | Unit | Medium | tests/security/confirmation-manager.test.js |\n 123→| E2E Main Chain | Integration | Critical | tests/integration/e2e-main-chain.test.js |\n 124→| Permission Flow | Integration | High | tests/integration/security-flow.test.js |\n 125→| Plan Version Flow | Integration | High | tests/integration/plan-version-flow.test.js |\n 126→\n 127→---\n 128→\n 129→## Decisions\n 130→\n 131→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 132→|----|------|----------|\n 133→| D1 | 2026-03-14 | 使用 Node.js 内置 test runner（与项目一致），不引入 Jest |\n 134→| D2 | 2026-03-14 | 集成测试使用 mock 替代真实 shell 脚本执行 |\n 135→| D3 | 2026-03-14 | 测试 fixtures 放置 tests/fixtures/ 目录 |\n 136→| D4 | 2026-03-14 | 不新建覆盖率工具，使用 node --test 内置能力 |\n 137→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdebebf5d85e280e638ca4e1c1068","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:12:57.775Z","_requestId":"f8b0d56a051a42089a34cee3b1b65359"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"2d71c62d-623b-41ce-b256-93152eae559c","session_id":"9310a036-0fcf-4395-9365-74ce968ab0f4","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cdebededfa54239ff44a0088c4538","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-007: Test and Validation Suite — Technical Plan\n   2→\n   3→## Architecture Overview\n   4→\n   5→```\n   6→tests/\n   7→├── fixtures/                    # Shared test data\n   8→│   ├── plans/                   # Sample plan files\n   9→│   │   ├── valid-feature-list.json\n  10→│   │   ├── valid-bug-fix-list.json\n  11→│   │   └── invalid-*.json       # Various invalid files\n  12→│   └── states/                  # Sample state files\n  13→│       ├── pipeline-idle.json\n  14→│       ├── pipeline-running.json\n  15→│       └── pipeline-completed.json\n  16→│\n  17→├── unit/                        # Pure unit tests (no I/O)\n  18→│   ├── bot/commands/\n  19→│   ├── services/\n  20→│   ├── security/\n  21→│   └── pipeline-infra/\n  22→│\n  23→├── integration/                 # Integration tests (with I/O mock)\n  24→│   ├── e2e-main-chain.test.js   # US-3: start → status → stop\n  25→│   ├── plan-version-flow.test.js\n  26→│   └── security-flow.test.js\n  27→│\n  28→└── helpers/                     # Test utilities\n  29→    ├── mock-runner.js           # Mock script runner\n  30→    ├── mock-telegram.js         # Mock Telegraf context\n  31→    └── test-state.js            # Temporary state management\n  32→```\n  33→\n  34→---\n  35→\n  36→## Component Design\n  37→\n  38→### C-1: Test Fixtures Module\n  39→\n  40→**Purpose**: Centralized test data management\n  41→\n  42→**Components**:\n  43→- `tests/fixtures/plans/` — Sample plan files for validation tests\n  44→- `tests/fixtures/states/` — Sample state files for pipeline tests\n  45→- `tests/helpers/fixture-loader.js` — Lazy loading utility\n  46→\n  47→**Interface**:\n  48→```typescript\n  49→// tests/helpers/fixture-loader.js\n  50→export function loadFixture(relativePath: string): string;\n  51→export function loadJsonFixture<T>(relativePath: string): T;\n  52→export function getFixturePath(relativePath: string): string;\n  53→```\n  54→\n  55→---\n  56→\n  57→### C-2: Mock Runner Module\n  58→\n  59→**Purpose**: Replace real shell execution with controlled responses\n  60→\n  61→**Interface**:\n  62→```typescript\n  63→// tests/helpers/mock-runner.js\n  64→export function createMockRunner(responses: MockResponseMap): MockRunner;\n  65→\n  66→interface MockResponseMap {\n  67→  [action: string]: MockResponse | MockResponse[];\n  68→}\n  69→\n  70→interface MockResponse {\n  71→  ok: boolean;\n  72→  data?: any;\n  73→  errorCode?: string;\n  74→  message?: string;\n  75→  delay?: number; // Simulate execution time\n  76→}\n  77→```\n  78→\n  79→**Usage**:\n  80→```javascript\n  81→const mockRunner = createMockRunner({\n  82→  'run': { ok: true, pid: 12345, runId: 'run-001' },\n  83→  'status': [\n  84→    { ok: true, isRunning: true, currentFeature: 'F-001' },\n  85→    { ok: true, isRunning: false, lastResult: 'completed' }\n  86→  ],\n  87→  'stop': { ok: true, previousPid: 12345 }\n  88→});\n  89→```\n  90→\n  91→---\n  92→\n  93→### C-3: Mock Telegram Context\n  94→\n  95→**Purpose**: Simulate Telegraf bot context for command handler tests\n  96→\n  97→**Interface**:\n  98→```typescript\n  99→// tests/helpers/mock-telegram.js\n 100→export function createMockContext(overrides?: Partial<MockContext>): MockContext;\n 101→\n 102→interface MockContext {\n 103→  message: { text?: string; document?: any; from: { id: number; username?: string } };\n 104→  chat: { id: number };\n 105→  reply: jest.Mock;\n 106→  replyWithDocument: jest.Mock;\n 107→  state: { permission?: PermissionLevel };\n 108→}\n 109→```\n 110→\n 111→---\n 112→\n 113→### C-4: Test State Manager\n 114→\n 115→**Purpose**: Manage temporary state files for integration tests\n 116→\n 117→**Interface**:\n 118→```typescript\n 119→// tests/helpers/test-state.js\n 120→export function createTestStateDir(prefix?: string): string;\n 121→export function cleanupTestStateDir(path: string): void;\n 122→export function writeTestState(path: string, data: object): void;\n 123→export function readTestState<T>(path: string): T | null;\n 124→```\n 125→\n 126→---\n 127→\n 128→## Interface Design\n 129→\n 130→### E2E Test Interface\n 131→\n 132→```typescript\n 133→// tests/integration/e2e-main-chain.test.js\n 134→\n 135→describe('E2E: Main Chain (start → status → stop)', () => {\n 136→  let mockRunner;\n 137→  let controller;\n 138→\n 139→  beforeEach(() => {\n 140→    mockRunner = createMockRunner(/* ... */);\n 141→    controller = createPipelineController({ runner: mockRunner });\n 142→  });\n 143→\n 144→  // Test cases...\n 145→});\n 146→```\n 147→\n 148→### Permission Test Interface\n 149→\n 150→```typescript\n 151→// tests/security/permission-guard.test.js\n 152→\n 153→describe('PermissionGuard', () => {\n 154→  describe('checkPermission', () => {\n 155→    it('should allow admin to execute any command', () => { /* ... */ });\n 156→    it('should block viewer from high-risk commands', () => { /* ... */ });\n 157→    it('should respect USER_PERMISSIONS config', () => { /* ... */ });\n 158→  });\n 159→\n 160→  describe('getMinPermission', () => {\n 161→    it('should return admin for stop/reset', () => { /* ... */ });\n 162→    it('should return operator for retry', () => { /* ... */ });\n 163→  });\n 164→});\n 165→```\n 166→\n 167→### Plan Validation Test Interface\n 168→\n 169→```typescript\n 170→// tests/services/plan-ingestion-service.test.js\n 171→\n 172→describe('PlanIngestionService', () => {\n 173→  describe('validate', () => {\n 174→    it('should accept valid feature-list', () => { /* ... */ });\n 175→    it('should reject missing $schema', () => { /* ... */ });\n 176→    it('should reject missing required fields', () => { /* ... */ });\n 177→  });\n 178→\n 179→  describe('version management', () => {\n 180→    it('should create new version on save', () => { /* ... */ });\n 181→    it('should switch active version', () => { /* ... */ });\n 182→    it('should rollback to previous version', () => { /* ... */ });\n 183→  });\n 184→});\n 185→```\n 186→\n 187→---\n 188→\n 189→## Data Model\n 190→\n 191→### Test Fixture Schema\n 192→\n 193→```json\n 194→// tests/fixtures/plans/valid-feature-list.json\n 195→{\n 196→  \"$schema\": \"dev-pipeline-feature-list-v1\",\n 197→  \"app_name\": \"TestApp\",\n 198→  \"features\": [\n 199→    { \"id\": \"F-TEST-001\", \"description\": \"Test feature\", \"status\": \"pending\" }\n 200→  ]\n 201→}\n 202→```\n 203→\n 204→```json\n 205→// tests/fixtures/states/pipeline-running.json\n 206→{\n 207→  \"isRunning\": true,\n 208→  \"pid\": 12345,\n 209→  \"currentFeature\": \"F-TEST-001\",\n 210→  \"startedAt\": \"2026-03-14T10:00:00Z\",\n 211→  \"completed\": [],\n 212→  \"failed\": []\n 213→}\n 214→```\n 215→\n 216→### Mock Response Schema\n 217→\n 218→```json\n 219→{\n 220→  \"ok\": true,\n 221→  \"runId\": \"run-001\",\n 222→  \"pid\": 12345,\n 223→  \"message\": \"Pipeline started\",\n 224→  \"data\": {\n 225→    \"isRunning\": true,\n 226→    \"currentFeature\": \"F-TEST-001\",\n 227→    \"startedAt\": \"2026-03-14T10:00:00Z\"\n 228→  }\n 229→}\n 230→```\n 231→\n 232→---\n 233→\n 234→## Test Strategy\n 235→\n 236→### Layer 1: Unit Tests (Pure)\n 237→\n 238→**Scope**: Functions without I/O dependencies\n 239→**Tools**: Node.js test runner + assert\n 240→**Mock Strategy**: Function injection, no file system\n 241→\n 242→**Target Files**:\n 243→- `tests/bot/commands/parser.test.js` — Command parsing logic\n 244→- `tests/bot/commands/validator.test.js` — Parameter validation\n 245→- `tests/security/param-sanitizer.test.js` — Sanitization rules\n 246→- `tests/pipeline-infra/error-codes.test.js` — Error mapping\n 247→\n 248→### Layer 2: Unit Tests (With Mock I/O)\n 249→\n 250→**Scope**: Functions with file/network dependencies\n 251→**Mock Strategy**: Mock fs, child_process, external APIs\n 252→\n 253→**Target Files**:\n 254→- `tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js` — Controller with mock runner\n 255→- `tests/services/plan-ingestion-service.test.js` — Service with temp dirs\n 256→- `tests/security/permission-guard.test.js` — Guard with mock config\n 257→\n 258→### Layer 3: Integration Tests\n 259→\n 260→**Scope**: Multiple components working together\n 261→**Mock Strategy**: Mock external services, use temp file system\n 262→\n 263→**Target Files**:\n 264→- `tests/integration/e2e-main-chain.test.js` — Full pipeline lifecycle\n 265→- `tests/integration/plan-version-flow.test.js` — Plan upload → activate\n 266→- `tests/integration/security-flow.test.js` — Permission check → confirmation\n 267→\n 268→---\n 269→\n 270→## Test Coverage Targets\n 271→\n 272→| Module | Current | Target | Gap |\n 273→|--------|---------|--------|-----|\n 274→| bot/commands/parser.js | ~70% | 90% | +20% |\n 275→| bot/commands/validator.js | ~60% | 85% | +25% |\n 276→| services/pipeline-controller.js | ~75% | 90% | +15% |\n 277→| services/plan-ingestion-service.js | ~80% | 90% | +10% |\n 278→| security/permission-guard.js | ~70% | 95% | +25% |\n 279→| security/param-sanitizer.js | ~65% | 90% | +25% |\n 280→| security/confirmation-manager.js | ~50% | 85% | +35% |\n 281→\n 282→---\n 283→\n 284→## Module Dependencies\n 285→\n 286→```\n 287→F-007 Test Suite\n 288→├── depends on → F-003 (plan-ingestion-service.js)\n 289→├── depends on → F-004 (pipeline-controller.js, lock-manager.js)\n 290→├── depends on → F-005 (status-aggregator.js, log-pager.js)\n 291→├── depends on → F-006 (permission-guard.js, param-sanitizer.js)\n 292→└── uses → Node.js test runner (built-in)\n 293→```\n 294→\n 295→---\n 296→\n 297→## Risk Assessment\n 298→\n 299→| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n 300→|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n 301→| Existing tests have gaps | Medium | Medium | Audit current coverage, prioritize missing cases |\n 302→| Mock strategy inconsistency | Low | Low | Create shared mock helpers |\n 303→| Integration tests flaky | Medium | Medium | Use deterministic mocks, avoid real I/O |\n 304→| Test data drift | Low | Medium | Version control fixtures, sync with schema |\n 305→\n 306→---\n 307→\n 308→## Testing the Tests\n 309→\n 310→**Self-Validation**:\n 311→- All tests pass on clean checkout\n 312→- Tests fail when expected (mutation testing mindset)\n 313→- No interdependencies between test files\n 314→- No shared mutable state\n 315→\n 316→**Quality Gates**:\n 317→```bash\n 318→# Run all tests\n 319→npm test\n 320→\n 321→# Run specific layer\n 322→node --test tests/unit/**/*.test.js\n 323→node --test tests/integration/*.test.js\n 324→```\n 325→\n 326→---\n 327→\n 328→## Decisions\n 329→\n 330→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 331→|----|------|----------|\n 332→| P1 | 2026-03-14 | 分层测试策略：纯单元 → Mock I/O → 集成 |\n 333→| P2 | 2026-03-14 | Mock runner 支持顺序响应模拟状态变化 |\n 334→| P3 | 2026-03-14 | 集成测试使用临时目录，测试后清理 |\n 335→| P4 | 2026-03-14 | Fixtures 与 schema 文件保持同步 |\n 336→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdebebf5d85e280e638ca4e1c1068","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:12:57.777Z","_requestId":"f8b0d56a051a42089a34cee3b1b65359"}
