{"type":"user","uuid":"7a9757a1-62be-438a-82a6-73678eb1f76c","session_id":"9310a036-0fcf-4395-9365-74ce968ab0f4","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cdec1021475a16704d072c3ff1e57","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Feature Registry\n   2→\n   3→| ID | Slug | Title | Status | Last Updated |\n   4→|----|------|-------|--------|--------------|\n   5→| F-001 | 001-project-infrastructure-setup | Project Infrastructure Setup | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   6→| F-002 | 002-telegram-pipeline-command-router | Telegram Pipeline Command Router | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   7→| F-003 | 003-feature-and-bug-plan-ingestion | Feature and Bug Plan Ingestion | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   8→| F-004 | 004-pipeline-process-controller | Pipeline Process Controller | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   9→| F-005 | 005-pipeline-status-and-log-streaming | Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming | completed | 2026-03-13 |\n  10→| F-006 | 006-safety-and-permission-guard | Safety and Permission Guard | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n  11→| F-007 | 007-test-and-validation-suite | Test and Validation Suite | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n  12→\n  13→## F-001: Project Infrastructure Setup\n  14→\n  15→**Status:** completed  \n  16→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  17→\n  18→### Deliverables\n  19→\n  20→- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` - Unified config loading with ENV/CLI override\n  21→- `src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js` - Feature/bug/session path resolution\n  22→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Error code definitions and factories\n  23→- `src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js` - Script execution wrapper\n  24→- `src/pipeline-infra/index.js` - Module entry point\n  25→- `src/services/pipeline-control-service.js` - High-level pipeline control API\n  26→- `dev-pipeline/scripts/path_policy.py` - Python path policy mirror\n  27→- Unit tests in `tests/pipeline-infra/` and `tests/services/`\n  28→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f001-user-stories.integration.test.js`\n  29→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm` and `.prizm-docs/pipeline/scripts.prizm`\n  30→\n  31→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  32→\n  33→- US-1: Unified config loading with readable validation errors\n  34→- US-2: Standard directory structure with Python/JS parity\n  35→- US-3: Unified script execution API (run/status/stop/logs/retry/reset)\n  36→- US-4: TypeScript and ESLint baseline established\n  37→\n  38→### Verification\n  39→\n  40→- `npm run typecheck`: 0 errors\n  41→- `npm run lint`: 0 warnings\n  42→- `npm test`: 29 tests pass\n  43→\n  44→---\n  45→\n  46→## F-002: Telegram Pipeline Command Router\n  47→\n  48→**Status:** completed  \n  49→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  50→\n  51→### Deliverables\n  52→\n  53→- `src/bot/commands/index.js` - Router entry point (auth, parse, validate, dispatch)\n  54→- `src/bot/commands/parser.js` - Command parsing with alias support\n  55→- `src/bot/commands/registry.js` - Dynamic command registration\n  56→- `src/bot/commands/validator.js` - Parameter validation\n  57→- `src/bot/commands/formatter.js` - User-friendly error messages\n  58→- `src/bot/commands/help.js` - Dynamic help text generation\n  59→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Pipeline command handler\n  60→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js` - Bugfix shortcut handler\n  61→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/planner.js` - Planner pipeline handler\n  62→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Status query handler\n  63→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Logs query handler\n  64→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Stop pipeline handler\n  65→- Unit tests in `tests/bot/commands/`\n  66→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f002-command-router.integration.test.js`\n  67→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm`\n  68→\n  69→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  70→\n  71→- US-1: Pipeline command with run/status/logs/stop subcommands\n  72→- US-2: Bugfix command as shortcut to `/pipeline run --type=bugfix`\n  73→- US-3: Status query showing all running pipelines\n  74→- US-4: Logs query with file fallback for large output\n  75→- US-5: Stop pipeline with confirmation\n  76→- US-6: Error guidance with clear suggestions\n  77→- US-7: Authorization guard on all commands\n  78→\n  79→### Commands Implemented\n  80→\n  81→| Command | Aliases | Description |\n  82→|---------|---------|-------------|\n  83→| `/pipeline` | `/p` | Manage pipelines (run/status/logs/stop) |\n  84→| `/bugfix` | `/b` | Start bugfix pipeline |\n  85→| `/planner` | — | Manage planner pipelines |\n  86→| `/status` | `/s` | Show running pipelines |\n  87→| `/logs` | `/l` | View pipeline logs |\n  88→| `/stop` | — | Stop running pipelines |\n  89→\n  90→### Verification\n  91→\n  92→- `npm test`: 105 tests pass (76 for F-002)\n  93→- Code review: PASS\n  94→- All 21 tasks completed\n  95→\n  96→---\n  97→\n  98→## F-003: Feature and Bug Plan Ingestion\n  99→\n 100→**Status:** completed  \n 101→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 102→\n 103→### Deliverables\n 104→\n 105→- `src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js` - Schema validation, version management, plan registry\n 106→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js` - Plan command handler (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n 107→- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Document upload handler for JSON files\n 108→- `src/services/pipeline-control-service.js` - Extended with resolvePlanListPath()\n 109→- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` - Extended with plansDir config\n 110→- `plans/` directory structure with feature-list/ and bug-fix-list/ subdirectories\n 111→- Unit tests in `tests/services/plan-ingestion-service.test.js`\n 112→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f003-plan-ingestion.integration.test.js`\n 113→\n 114→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 115→\n 116→- US-1: Upload Plan File - Telegram document message handling with auto-type detection\n 117→- US-2: Schema Validation - Ajv-based validation with field-level error messages\n 118→- US-3: Version Management - Timestamp-based versioning with use/rollback commands\n 119→- US-4: Plan Status Query - Status command showing version info and content summary\n 120→- US-5: Plan Integrity Protection - Validation precedes save, current version preserved on error\n 121→- US-6: Pipeline Integration - resolvePlanListPath() for dynamic plan path resolution\n 122→\n 123→### Commands Implemented\n 124→\n 125→| Command | Subcommands | Description |\n 126→|---------|-------------|-------------|\n 127→| `/plan` | status, versions, use, rollback, validate | Manage plan files |\n 128→\n 129→### Verification\n 130→\n 131→- Code review: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS\n 132→- All 18 tasks completed\n 133→- Unit tests: 19 passing\n 134→- Integration tests: 10 passing\n 135→\n 136→---\n 137→\n 138→## F-004: Pipeline Process Controller\n 139→\n 140→**Status:** completed\n 141→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 142→\n 143→### Deliverables\n 144→\n 145→- `src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js` - File-based lock management with PID validation\n 146→- `src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js` - State file reading/writing for daemon and pipeline state\n 147→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 6 new error codes for F-004\n 148→- `src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js` - Extended with lock/state path resolvers\n 149→- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Unified pipeline control API with concurrency protection\n 150→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 151→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 152→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 153→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 154→- Unit tests in `tests/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.test.js` and `tests/pipeline-infra/state-manager.test.js`\n 155→- Unit tests in `tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js`\n 156→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js`\n 157→\n 158→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 159→\n 160→- US-1: Unified Pipeline Start - startPipeline with daemon/foreground modes, lock acquisition\n 161→- US-2: Pipeline Stop - stopPipeline with ALREADY_STOPPED handling, lock release\n 162→- US-3: Target Retry - retryTarget with validation and mode support\n 163→- US-4: Run Single Feature - runSingle without lock (independent execution)\n 164→- US-5: Status Query - getStatus with daemon/pipeline state, lastResult\n 165→- US-6: Logs Query - getLogs with line limit, missing file handling\n 166→- US-7: Concurrency Protection - lock-manager with stale lock cleanup, forceUnlock\n 167→- US-8: Error Mapping - Consistent error codes with hint/context fields\n 168→- US-9: Telegram Handler Integration - All handlers updated to use pipeline-controller\n 169→\n 170→### Error Codes Added\n 171→\n 172→| Code | Description |\n 173→|------|-------------|\n 174→| LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED | Pipeline already running |\n 175→| ALREADY_STOPPED | Pipeline not running |\n 176→| PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING | No active pipeline |\n 177→| INVALID_TARGET | Missing or invalid target ID |\n 178→| TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE | Target state not retryable |\n 179→| DAEMON_START_FAILED | Failed to start daemon |\n 180→\n 181→### Key Decisions\n 182→\n 183→- D1: File lock + PID validation for concurrency protection (no external dependencies)\n 184→- D2: Separate lock-manager module for single responsibility\n 185→- D3: Reuse existing state files (backward compatible)\n 186→- D4: New pipeline-controller module vs extending pipeline-control-service\n 187→- D5: runSingle does NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\n 188→\n 189→### Verification\n 190→\n 191→- Code review: PASS\n 192→- 128 of 143 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n 193→- Unit tests: 80+ passing\n 194→- Integration tests: 20+ passing\n 195→\n 196→---\n 197→\n 198→## F-005: Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming\n 199→\n 200→**Status:** completed\n 201→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-13\n 202→\n 203→### Deliverables\n 204→\n 205→- `src/services/status-aggregator.js` - Aggregates state from multiple sources for unified status view\n 206→- `src/services/log-pager.js` - Paginated log reading with streaming support for large files\n 207→- `src/services/telegram-pusher.js` - Telegram message pushing with throttling, chunking, heartbeat\n 208→- `src/services/index.js` - Exports all new services\n 209→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated with aggregated status and --type parameter\n 210→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated with pagination (--lines, --offset, --file)\n 211→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 8 new error codes for F-005\n 212→- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Extended with lifecycle hooks (on/off/emit)\n 213→- Unit tests in `tests/services/status-aggregator.test.js`, `tests/services/log-pager.test.js`, `tests/services/telegram-pusher.test.js`\n 214→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f005-status-and-logs.integration.test.js`\n 215→\n 216→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 217→\n 218→- US-1: Aggregated Status Query - /status shows running/paused/completed/failed/idle state with progress\n 219→- US-2: Paginated Logs Query - /logs with --lines, --offset, --type parameters (max 500 lines)\n 220→- US-3: Message Length Compliance - Auto-chunking at 4000 chars with [N/M] segment numbering\n 221→- US-4: Heartbeat Progress Push - Event-driven heartbeat with 30s throttle\n 222→- US-5: Error Summary Push - Error notifications with log lines and duration\n 223→- US-6: Diagnostic Error Messages - Friendly messages for missing/corrupted state files\n 224→\n 225→### Commands Enhanced\n 226→\n 227→| Command | New Parameters | Description |\n 228→|---------|----------------|-------------|\n 229→| `/status` | `--type=feature\\|bugfix` | Aggregated pipeline status |\n 230→| `/logs` | `--lines=N --offset=N --type=feature\\|bugfix --file` | Paginated log viewing |\n 231→\n 232→### Error Codes Added\n 233→\n 234→| Code | Description |\n 235→|------|-------------|\n 236→| STATE_FILE_MISSING | State file not found |\n 237→| STATE_FILE_CORRUPTED | JSON parse error |\n 238→| LOG_FILE_MISSING | Log file not found |\n 239→| LOG_READ_ERROR | Log read failure |\n 240→| SEND_FAILED | Telegram send failure |\n 241→| FILE_SEND_FAILED | File send failure |\n 242→| HEARTBEAT_DISABLED | Heartbeat not enabled |\n 243→| INVALID_PIPELINE_TYPE | Invalid pipeline type |\n 244→\n 245→### Key Decisions\n 246→\n 247→- D1: Independent status-aggregator service (single responsibility)\n 248→- D2: In-memory message queue with retry (non-blocking)\n 249→- D3: CLI argument pagination (simple, no complex protocol)\n 250→- D4: Event-driven heartbeat + time throttle (30s minimum interval)\n 251→- D5: Real-time error extraction from logs (no additional storage)\n 252→- D6: Lifecycle hooks via EventEmitter in pipeline-controller\n 253→- D7: Message retry: max 3, exponential backoff (1s → 2s → 4s)\n 254→\n 255→### Verification\n 256→\n 257→- All 77 tasks completed\n 258→- Unit tests: 120+ passing\n 259→- Integration tests: 15+ passing\n 260→- NFR-1: Status aggregation < 200ms, log read < 300ms\n 261→- NFR-2: Push failures don't block pipeline (queue + retry)\n 262→- NFR-3: Test coverage > 85%\n 263→\n 264→---\n 265→\n 266→## F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n 267→\n 268→**Status:** completed\n 269→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 270→\n 271→### Deliverables\n 272→\n 273→- `src/security/permission-guard.js` - Three-tier permission model (admin/operator/viewer) with env config\n 274→- `src/security/param-sanitizer.js` - Parameter sanitization with path traversal and shell injection protection\n 275→- `src/security/confirmation-manager.js` - Text-based confirmation flow with 60s timeout\n 276→- `src/security/guard.js` - Unified guard middleware for command handlers\n 277→- `src/security/system-guard.js` - System exec command guard with ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC control\n 278→- `src/security/index.js` -