on\n 313→- D4: --force flag only for admin users\n 314→\n 315→### Verification\n 316→\n 317→- Code review: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS\n 318→- All 22 tasks completed\n 319→- Unit tests: 90+ passing\n 320→- Integration tests: 43+ passing\n 321→\n 322→---\n 323→\n 324→## F-007: Test and Validation Suite\n 325→\n 326→**Status:** completed  \n 327→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 328→\n 329→### Deliverables\n 330→\n 331→- `tests/fixtures/plans/` - Valid and invalid plan file fixtures for validation tests\n 332→- `tests/fixtures/states/` - Pipeline state fixtures (idle, running, completed, failed)\n 333→- `tests/helpers/fixture-loader.js` - Lazy-loading utility for test fixtures\n 334→- `tests/helpers/mock-runner.js` - Mock script runner with response sequencing\n 335→- `tests/helpers/mock-telegram.js` - Mock Telegraf context for command handler tests\n 336→- `tests/helpers/test-state.js` - Temporary state management for integration tests\n 337→- `tests/integration/e2e-main-chain.test.js` - E2E test for start → status → stop main chain\n 338→- `tests/integration/plan-version-flow.test.js` - Integration test for plan version management\n 339→- Enhanced tests in `tests/bot/commands/`, `tests/services/`, `tests/security/`\n 340→\n 341→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 342→\n 343→- US-1: Command Parsing & Routing Tests - Parser, registry, validator, formatter coverage\n 344→- US-2: Control Layer Return Tests - Pipeline control service, controller, plan ingestion coverage\n 345→- US-3: E2E Integration Test - start → status → stop main chain with state transitions\n 346→- US-4: Plan File Validation Tests - Schema validation, version management, dynamic switching\n 347→- US-5: Permission & Security Negative Tests - Permission boundaries, param sanitization, confirmation flow\n 348→\n 349→### Test Infrastructure\n 350→\n 351→| Component | Tests | Status |\n 352→|-----------|-------|--------|\n 353→| Test helpers (4 files) | 31 | ✅ Pass |\n 354→| E2E main chain | 10 | ✅ Pass |\n 355→| Plan version flow | 17 | ✅ Pass |\n 356→| Enhanced unit tests | 150+ | ✅ Pass |\n 357→\n 358→### Key Decisions\n 359→\n 360→- D1: Use Node.js built-in test runner (no Jest)\n 361→- D2: Mock runner supports response sequencing for state transitions\n 362→- D3: Integration tests use temp directories with cleanup\n 363→- D4: Fixtures version-controlled alongside schema files\n 364→\n 365→### Verification\n 366→\n 367→- Code review: PASS\n 368→- 37 of 40 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n 369→- Test suite: 200+ tests passing\n 370→- NFR-1: Unit tests < 10s, Integration tests < 60s\n 371→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdec1021475a16704d072c3ff1e57","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:15:17.380Z","_requestId":"f8b0d56a051a42089a34cee3b1b65359"}
